     (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});
</script></div>

<h2><span id="List_of_Anti-Piracy_Weapons_In_Ships">List of Anti-Piracy Weapons In Ships</span></h2>
<p>Here is the list of the most high-tech anti-piracy weapons deployed in ships to fight pirates.</p>
<h3><span id="1_Anti-Piracy_Laser_Device">1) Anti-Piracy Laser Device</span></h3>
<div id="attachment_8297" style="width: 760px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-8297" class="size-full wp-image-8297" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20750%20500'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Anti-Pirate Laser" width="750" height="500" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/laser-anti-piracy-device.jpg 750w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/laser-anti-piracy-device-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/laser-anti-piracy-device-150x100.jpg 150w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/laser-anti-piracy-device-500x333.jpg 500w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/laser-anti-piracy-device-20x13.jpg 20w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px" title="20 Anti-Piracy Weapons Deployed In Ships To Fight Pirates 15" data-lazy-src="https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/laser-anti-piracy-device.jpg"><noscript><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-8297" class="size-full wp-image-8297" src="https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/laser-anti-piracy-device.jpg" alt="Anti-Pirate Laser" width="750" height="500" srcset="https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/laser-anti-piracy-device.jpg 750w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/laser-anti-piracy-device-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/laser-anti-piracy-device-150x100.jpg 150w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/laser-anti-piracy-device-500x333.jpg 500w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/laser-anti-piracy-device-20x13.jpg 20w" sizes="(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px" title="20 Anti-Piracy Weapons Deployed In Ships To Fight Pirates 15"></noscript><p id="caption-attachment-8297" class="wp-caption-text">Anti-Pirate Laser</p><div class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px 0; clear: both;'>
<script type="rocketlazyloadscript" async src="https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script>
<!-- maritime body display ads -->
<ins class="adsbygoogle"
     style="display:block"
     data-ad-client="ca-pub-8158074151468920"
     data-ad-slot="7233289586"
     data-ad-format="auto"
     data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins>
<script type="rocketlazyloadscript">
     (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});
</script></div>
</div>
<p><a href="https://www.economist.com/babbage/2011/01/14/anti-piracy-laser" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow"><strong>Anti-Piracy Laser Device</strong></a> is a device developed by a British firm called <strong>BAE systems</strong>. It is a laser which can be used during commercial shipping against piracy. It is effective at a distance of about 1.5 km. it is used to distract the pirates in order to make them incapable of aiming properly without permanently damaging their eyes. It can be called as a warning device. Normal sunglasses cannot filter out this light and hence they will not help in avoiding it.</p>
<h3><span id="2_Water_Cannon">2) Water Cannon</span></h3>
<div id="attachment_8298" style="width: 760px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-8298" class="size-full wp-image-8298" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20750%20500'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Water Cannon" width="750" height="500" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/water-cannon.jpg 750w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/water-cannon-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/water-cannon-150x100.jpg 150w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/water-cannon-500x333.jpg 500w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/water-cannon-20x13.jpg 20w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px" title="20 Anti-Piracy Weapons Deployed In Ships To Fight Pirates 16" data-lazy-src="https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/water-cannon.jpg"><noscript><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-8298" class="size-full wp-image-8298" src="https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/water-cannon.jpg" alt="Water Cannon" width="750" height="500" srcset="https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/water-cannon.jpg 750w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/water-cannon-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/water-cannon-150x100.jpg 150w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/water-cannon-500x333.jpg 500w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/water-cannon-20x13.jpg 20w" sizes="(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px" title="20 Anti-Piracy Weapons Deployed In Ships To Fight Pirates 16"></noscript><p id="caption-attachment-8298" class="wp-caption-text">Photo courtesy: https://www.flickr.com/photos/guano/3264971746</p><div class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px 0; clear: both;'>
<script type="rocketlazyloadscript" async src="https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script>
<!-- maritime body display ads -->
<ins class="adsbygoogle"
     style="display:block"
     data-ad-client="ca-pub-8158074151468920"
     data-ad-slot="7233289586"
     data-ad-format="auto"
     data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins>
<script type="rocketlazyloadscript">
     (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});
</script></div>
</div>
<p>A water cannon is an anti-piracy device <strong>(non-lethal)</strong> normally used on merchant ships. This device can shoot a high-velocity stream of water which is impenetrable. it is so strong that it can blow away the pirates which are trying to come on board the ship. It can also fill up the enemy ship with water to decrease their speed and disturb their maneuverability. This is a very powerful system but still non-lethal.</p>
<p>The device usually consists of a powerful water cannon placed strategically all around the ship. They draw the seawater and can be easily controlled from the bridge. This weapon is also highly effective in controlling fires and contributing to the overall safety of the vessel.</p><div class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px 0; clear: both;'>
<script type="rocketlazyloadscript" async src="https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script>
