<h3><span id="4_Nets_or_Boat_Traps">4) Nets or Boat Traps</span></h3>
<p>A boat trap is a kind of system which is used to stop pirates and their boats when they come closer to a merchant vessel. It is a ballistic net. It is a good system that can help in the defense of a vessel while avoiding the need to use guns or other such lethal weapons and posing threat to the crew or other people if it is near a harbor. Destructive and extensively tested in the Caribbean and US waters. Most of the time, they are used to entrap smaller boats that may be operated by terrorists, pirates, or smugglers. It is an efficient system to be used in crowded areas such as the Gulf of Aden.</p><div class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px 0; clear: both;'>
<script type="rocketlazyloadscript" async src="https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script>
<!-- maritime body display ads -->
<ins class="adsbygoogle"
     style="display:block"
     data-ad-client="ca-pub-8158074151468920"
     data-ad-slot="7233289586"
     data-ad-format="auto"
     data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins>
<script type="rocketlazyloadscript">
     (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});
</script></div>

<h3><span id="5_Slippery_Foam_or_Mobile_Denial_System">5) Slippery Foam or Mobile Denial System</span></h3>
<p>Mobile Dual System or a Mobility Denial System is a non-lethal strategy used to slow down the movement of trespassers rather, avoid them from climbing the decks of a ship. Slippery foam or substance is used to make the deck of a ship slippery and therefore how to walk or stand on. This substance has a high viscosity. The substances also normally non-lethal. this method is being highly used by military and security forces.</p>
<h3><span id="6_Long_Range_Acoustic_Device">6) Long Range Acoustic Device</span></h3>
<div id="attachment_8299" style="width: 650px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-8299" class="size-full wp-image-8299" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20640%20426'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Long Range Acoustic Device - LARD" width="640" height="426" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Long-Range-Acoustic-Device-LARD.jpg 640w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Long-Range-Acoustic-Device-LARD-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Long-Range-Acoustic-Device-LARD-150x100.jpg 150w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Long-Range-Acoustic-Device-LARD-500x333.jpg 500w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Long-Range-Acoustic-Device-LARD-20x13.jpg 20w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" title="20 Anti-Piracy Weapons Deployed In Ships To Fight Pirates 18" data-lazy-src="https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Long-Range-Acoustic-Device-LARD.jpg"><noscript><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-8299" class="size-full wp-image-8299" src="https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Long-Range-Acoustic-Device-LARD.jpg" alt="Long Range Acoustic Device - LARD" width="640" height="426" srcset="https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Long-Range-Acoustic-Device-LARD.jpg 640w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Long-Range-Acoustic-Device-LARD-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Long-Range-Acoustic-Device-LARD-150x100.jpg 150w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Long-Range-Acoustic-Device-LARD-500x333.jpg 500w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Long-Range-Acoustic-Device-LARD-20x13.jpg 20w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" title="20 Anti-Piracy Weapons Deployed In Ships To Fight Pirates 18"></noscript><p id="caption-attachment-8299" class="wp-caption-text">Long Range Acoustic Device – LARD</p><div class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px 0; clear: both;'>
<script type="rocketlazyloadscript" async src="https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script>
<!-- maritime body display ads -->
<ins class="adsbygoogle"
     style="display:block"
     data-ad-client="ca-pub-8158074151468920"
     data-ad-slot="7233289586"
     data-ad-format="auto"
     data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins>
<script type="rocketlazyloadscript">
     (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});
</script></div>
</div>
<p>Abbreviated as LRAD, a Long Range Acoustic Device is a device that is capable of emitting a 151 dB sound. It can do so within 30 degrees of wherever the device is pointing. It is used to drive away pirates. It was developed by an American technology corporation. It can produce a high-pitched sound that is painful to human ears. In fact, it can cause permanent ear damage. It was about 210 kilograms and has a range of about 300 to 500 meters.</p>
<p>It is mainly used by the military but has also been used on some cargo and <a href="https://www.maritimemanual.com/what-is-a-cruise-ship/">cruise ships</a>. The sound wave can be canceled with the help of normal earplugs and hence minimize its effect. This is one of the biggest disadvantages of the device.</p><div class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px 0; clear: both;'>
<script type="rocketlazyloadscript" async src="https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script>
<!-- maritime body display ads -->
<ins class="adsbygoogle"
     style="display:block"
     data-ad-client="ca-pub-8158074151468920"
     data-ad-slot="7233289586"
     data-ad-format="auto"
     data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins>
<script type="rocketlazyloadscript">
     (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});
</script></div>

<h3><span id="7_Foul_Smelling_Liquid_or_Liquid_Deterrent_System">7) Foul Smelling Liquid or Liquid Deterrent System</span></h3>
<p>The system comes from the International Maritime Security Network of the United States. In the system, the approaching pirates are showered with a foul-smelling liquid. This liquid is capable of stinking and burning. It causes such a burning sensation and emits such a foul smell that the pirates feel the need to jump into the water and hence it prevents a pirate attack.</p>
<p>The substances are usually shot towards the target with the help of a stun gun. It is similar to a taser gun except that the use of liquid streams. This is a non-lethal system normally used in the areas in and around the Gulf of Aden.</p><div class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px 0; clear: both;'>
<script type="rocketlazyloadscript" async src="https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script>
<!-- maritime body display ads -->
<ins class="adsbygoogle"
     style="display:block"
     data-ad-client="ca-pub-8158074151468920"
     data-ad-slot="7233289586"
     data-ad-format="auto"
     data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins>
<script type="rocketlazyloadscript">
     (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});
</script></div>

<h3><span id="8_Razor_Wire_Canister_or_Anti-boarding_Device">8) Razor Wire Canister or Anti-boarding Device</span></h3>
<div id="attachment_8302" style="width: 810px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-8302" class="size-full wp-image-8302" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20800%20600'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Anti-boarding Device" width="800" height="600" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/anti-boarding-device.jpg 800w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/anti-boarding-device-300x225.jpg 300w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/anti-boarding-device-768x576.jpg 768w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/anti-boarding-device-150x113.jpg 150w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/anti-boarding-device-500x375.jpg 500w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/anti-boarding-device-20x15.jpg 20w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px" title="20 Anti-Piracy Weapons Deployed In Ships To Fight Pirates 19" data-lazy-src="https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/anti-boarding-device.jpg"><noscript><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-8302" class="size-full wp-image-8302" src="https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/anti-boarding-device.jpg" alt="Anti-boarding Device" width="800" height="600" srcset="https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/anti-boarding-device.jpg 800w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/anti-boarding-device-300x225.jpg 300w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/anti-boarding-device-768x576.jpg 768w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/anti-boarding-device-150x113.jpg 150w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/anti-boarding-device-500x375.jpg 500w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/anti-boarding-device-20x15.jpg 20w" sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px" title="20 Anti-Piracy Weapons Deployed In Ships To Fight Pirates 19"></noscript><p id="caption-attachment-8302" class="wp-caption-text">Anti-boarding Device: Photo courtesy: http://vpsystems.co.za</p></div>
<p>Razor wire canister or an antibonding device is another anti-piracy system. It prevents pirates from boarding the vessel with the help of canisters with sharp razor wires. This is currently the most commonly used anti-piracy deterrent. Razor wire is installed around the perimeter of a ship. This wire acts as a wall or a barrier between the ship and those wanting to trespass.</p><div class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px 0; clear: both;'>
<script type="rocketlazyloadscript" async src="https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script>
<!-- maritime body display ads -->
<ins class="adsbygoogle"
     style="display:block"
     data-ad-client="ca-pub-8158074151468920"
     data-ad-slot="7233289586"
     data-ad-format="auto"
     data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins>
<script type="rocketlazyloadscript">
     (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});
</script></div>

<p>This restricts the movement of pirates onto the ship considerably. However, this method is somewhat disadvantageous as there is always a fear of a crew member getting injured or infected by handling the razor wires.</p><div class="mailmunch-forms-in-post-middle" style="display: none !important;"></div>
<p>Photo courtesy: <a href="http://vpsystems.co.za" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">http://vpsystems.co.za</a></p><div class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px 0; clear: both;'>
<script type="rocketlazyloadscript" async src="https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script>
<!-- maritime body display ads -->
