<h3><span id="9_Compressed_Air_-_Ship_Borne_Shore_Launcher">9) Compressed Air – Ship Borne Shore Launcher</span></h3>
<div id="attachment_8301" style="width: 412px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-8301" class="size-full wp-image-8301" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20402%20450'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Compressed Air Gun" width="402" height="450" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/compressed-air-gun.jpg 402w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/compressed-air-gun-268x300.jpg 268w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/compressed-air-gun-150x168.jpg 150w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/compressed-air-gun-18x20.jpg 18w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 402px) 100vw, 402px" title="20 Anti-Piracy Weapons Deployed In Ships To Fight Pirates 20" data-lazy-src="https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/compressed-air-gun.jpg"><noscript><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-8301" class="size-full wp-image-8301" src="https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/compressed-air-gun.jpg" alt="Compressed Air Gun" width="402" height="450" srcset="https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/compressed-air-gun.jpg 402w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/compressed-air-gun-268x300.jpg 268w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/compressed-air-gun-150x168.jpg 150w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/compressed-air-gun-18x20.jpg 18w" sizes="(max-width: 402px) 100vw, 402px" title="20 Anti-Piracy Weapons Deployed In Ships To Fight Pirates 20"></noscript><p id="caption-attachment-8301" class="wp-caption-text">Compressed Air Gun</p></div>
<p>A product of a UK-based company, a Ship Borne Shore Launcher is an anti-piracy system consisting of a cannon-shaped device. This device uses compressed air in order to fire a variety of projectiles. It is generally a non-lethal system. However, it can be very powerful or even lethal depending upon the distance in which it is operating. It normally has a range of more than 400 m. This system is accepted as an important safety and survival system. Much like any other anti-piracy system this system is also used extensively in and around the Gulf of Aden.</p><div class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px 0; clear: both;'>
<script type="rocketlazyloadscript" async src="https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script>
