<h3><span id="10_P-Trap_Anti-Piracy_System">10) P-Trap Anti-Piracy System</span></h3>
<div id="attachment_8304" style="width: 748px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-8304" class="size-full wp-image-8304" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20738%20417'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="P-Trap Anti-Piracy System" width="738" height="417" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/P-Trap-Anti-Piracy-System.jpg 738w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/P-Trap-Anti-Piracy-System-300x170.jpg 300w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/P-Trap-Anti-Piracy-System-150x85.jpg 150w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/P-Trap-Anti-Piracy-System-500x283.jpg 500w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/P-Trap-Anti-Piracy-System-20x11.jpg 20w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 738px) 100vw, 738px" title="20 Anti-Piracy Weapons Deployed In Ships To Fight Pirates 21" data-lazy-src="https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/P-Trap-Anti-Piracy-System.jpg"><noscript><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-8304" class="size-full wp-image-8304" src="https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/P-Trap-Anti-Piracy-System.jpg" alt="P-Trap Anti-Piracy System" width="738" height="417" srcset="https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/P-Trap-Anti-Piracy-System.jpg 738w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/P-Trap-Anti-Piracy-System-300x170.jpg 300w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/P-Trap-Anti-Piracy-System-150x85.jpg 150w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/P-Trap-Anti-Piracy-System-500x283.jpg 500w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/P-Trap-Anti-Piracy-System-20x11.jpg 20w" sizes="(max-width: 738px) 100vw, 738px" title="20 Anti-Piracy Weapons Deployed In Ships To Fight Pirates 21"></noscript><p id="caption-attachment-8304" class="wp-caption-text">P-Trap Anti-Piracy System</p></div>
<p>P-Trap Anti-Piracy System is a simple and yet effective measure against piracy. It is non-lethal. It consists of floating lines creating a safety zone around the vessel. This floating line can trap propellers of pirate vessels. These lines are so small that are almost invisible and are thrown directly under the surface of the ocean.</p><div class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px 0; clear: both;'>
<script type="rocketlazyloadscript" async src="https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script>
<!-- maritime body display ads -->
<ins class="adsbygoogle"
     style="display:block"
     data-ad-client="ca-pub-8158074151468920"
     data-ad-slot="7233289586"
     data-ad-format="auto"
     data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins>
<script type="rocketlazyloadscript">
     (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});
</script></div>

<p>Once installed this system can be used without monitoring at any time of the day. This is considered as one of the best anti-piracy systems as it provides additional security to the crew members, can be used in all kinds of weather conditions, and is very simple to install and apply in vessels without the involvement of the crew.</p>
<h3><span id="11_Anti-Piracy_Curtain">11) Anti-Piracy Curtain</span></h3>
<div id="attachment_8305" style="width: 501px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-8305" class="size-full wp-image-8305" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20491%20327'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Anti-Piracy Curtain" width="491" height="327" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/anti-piracy-curtain.jpg 491w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/anti-piracy-curtain-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/anti-piracy-curtain-150x100.jpg 150w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/anti-piracy-curtain-20x13.jpg 20w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 491px) 100vw, 491px" title="20 Anti-Piracy Weapons Deployed In Ships To Fight Pirates 22" data-lazy-src="https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/anti-piracy-curtain.jpg"><noscript><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-8305" class="size-full wp-image-8305" src="https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/anti-piracy-curtain.jpg" alt="Anti-Piracy Curtain" width="491" height="327" srcset="https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/anti-piracy-curtain.jpg 491w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/anti-piracy-curtain-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/anti-piracy-curtain-150x100.jpg 150w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/anti-piracy-curtain-20x13.jpg 20w" sizes="(max-width: 491px) 100vw, 491px" title="20 Anti-Piracy Weapons Deployed In Ships To Fight Pirates 22"></noscript><p id="caption-attachment-8305" class="wp-caption-text">Anti-Piracy Curtain</p><div class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px 0; clear: both;'>
<script type="rocketlazyloadscript" async src="https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script>
<!-- maritime body display ads -->
<ins class="adsbygoogle"
     style="display:block"
     data-ad-client="ca-pub-8158074151468920"
     data-ad-slot="7233289586"
     data-ad-format="auto"
     data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins>
<script type="rocketlazyloadscript">
     (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});
</script></div>
</div>
<p>An anti-piracy curtain is a system which consists of a series of hoses being dangled out from the sides of a vessel. They are weighed to keep themselves close to the surface of the water. When water is pumped through the hoses, they fling around violently, making it difficult for possible trespassers to board the ship. The force is nearly 0.2 megapascal. This method is often employed in commercial ships and vessels as they are not allowed to carry arms in international waters. Hence, it is a non-lethal anti-piracy system that can be used by all without any difficulty.</p>
<h3><span id="12_Maritime_Early_Detection_System">12) Maritime Early Detection System</span></h3>
<div id="attachment_8306" style="width: 575px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-8306" class="size-full wp-image-8306" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20565%20390'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Maritime Early Detection System" width="565" height="390" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/anti-piracy-maritime-systems.jpg 565w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/anti-piracy-maritime-systems-300x207.jpg 300w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/anti-piracy-maritime-systems-150x104.jpg 150w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/anti-piracy-maritime-systems-500x345.jpg 500w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/anti-piracy-maritime-systems-20x14.jpg 20w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 565px) 100vw, 565px" title="20 Anti-Piracy Weapons Deployed In Ships To Fight Pirates 23" data-lazy-src="https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/anti-piracy-maritime-systems.jpg"><noscript><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-8306" class="size-full wp-image-8306" src="https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/anti-piracy-maritime-systems.jpg" alt="Maritime Early Detection System" width="565" height="390" srcset="https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/anti-piracy-maritime-systems.jpg 565w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/anti-piracy-maritime-systems-300x207.jpg 300w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/anti-piracy-maritime-systems-150x104.jpg 150w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/anti-piracy-maritime-systems-500x345.jpg 500w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/anti-piracy-maritime-systems-20x14.jpg 20w" sizes="(max-width: 565px) 100vw, 565px" title="20 Anti-Piracy Weapons Deployed In Ships To Fight Pirates 23"></noscript><p id="caption-attachment-8306" class="wp-caption-text">Maritime Early Detection System. Pics: https://www.monitor-systems-engineering.com/anti_piracy_terrorism_maritime_security_specialist_partner_products.html</p><div class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px 0; clear: both;'>
<script type="rocketlazyloadscript" async src="https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script>
<!-- maritime body display ads -->
<ins class="adsbygoogle"
     style="display:block"
     data-ad-client="ca-pub-8158074151468920"
     data-ad-slot="7233289586"
     data-ad-format="auto"
     data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins>
<script type="rocketlazyloadscript">
     (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});
</script></div>
</div>
<p>A Maritime Early Detection System is not exactly a weapon, but it can be equipped to provide active deterrence. It is a system consisting of a sensor network with infrared tracking vision cameras working day and night in addition to the onboard radar equipment. The system can be used to detect the presence of any other shape or vessel nearby and take action against it if it turns out to be a threat.</p>
<h3><span id="13_Superfly">13) Superfly</span></h3>
<p>Superfly is an unmanned non-lethal air vehicle. It is an extra watch stander that keeps a vigilant eye on the horizon which is beyond the limits of human eyesight. It is a small and easily portable device and is cost-effective at the same time. It is very effective in looking for other vessels nearby and then takes the necessary precautions or actions if required.</p><div class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px 0; clear: both;'>
<script type="rocketlazyloadscript" async src="https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script>
