<h3><span id="14_Rubber_Ball_Grenade">14) Rubber Ball Grenade</span></h3>
<div id="attachment_8307" style="width: 438px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-8307" class="size-full wp-image-8307" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20428%20531'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Rubber Ball Grenade " width="428" height="531" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/rubber-ball-grenade.jpg 428w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/rubber-ball-grenade-242x300.jpg 242w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/rubber-ball-grenade-150x186.jpg 150w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/rubber-ball-grenade-403x500.jpg 403w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/rubber-ball-grenade-16x20.jpg 16w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 428px) 100vw, 428px" title="20 Anti-Piracy Weapons Deployed In Ships To Fight Pirates 24" data-lazy-src="https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/rubber-ball-grenade.jpg"><noscript><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-8307" class="size-full wp-image-8307" src="https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/rubber-ball-grenade.jpg" alt="Rubber Ball Grenade " width="428" height="531" srcset="https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/rubber-ball-grenade.jpg 428w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/rubber-ball-grenade-242x300.jpg 242w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/rubber-ball-grenade-150x186.jpg 150w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/rubber-ball-grenade-403x500.jpg 403w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/rubber-ball-grenade-16x20.jpg 16w" sizes="(max-width: 428px) 100vw, 428px" title="20 Anti-Piracy Weapons Deployed In Ships To Fight Pirates 24"></noscript><p id="caption-attachment-8307" class="wp-caption-text">Rubber Ball Grenade – Pics courtesy: http://www.defense-technology.com/products/tactical-devices/stinger-32-caliber-rubber-ball-grenade-1011582.html</p></div>
<p><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grenade" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">Rubber ball grenades</a> are a very effective measure against piracy. They are non-lethal weapons that spray rubber bullets on detonation. they are also capable of producing lights and sounds in order to deter the pirates from approaching the ship or vessel. They are also called sting ball grenades. These grenades can cause serious injuries. They are normally used in defense and military matters.</p><div class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px 0; clear: both;'>
<script type="rocketlazyloadscript" async src="https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script>
