<h3><span id="15_Active_Denial_System_-_Pain_Ray_Electromagnetic_wave">15) Active Denial System – Pain Ray (Electromagnetic wave)</span></h3>
<div id="attachment_8308" style="width: 643px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-8308" class="size-full wp-image-8308" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20633%20422'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Active Denial System" width="633" height="422" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/active-denial-system.jpg 633w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/active-denial-system-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/active-denial-system-150x100.jpg 150w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/active-denial-system-500x333.jpg 500w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/active-denial-system-20x13.jpg 20w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 633px) 100vw, 633px" title="20 Anti-Piracy Weapons Deployed In Ships To Fight Pirates 25" data-lazy-src="https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/active-denial-system.jpg"><noscript><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-8308" class="size-full wp-image-8308" src="https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/active-denial-system.jpg" alt="Active Denial System" width="633" height="422" srcset="https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/active-denial-system.jpg 633w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/active-denial-system-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/active-denial-system-150x100.jpg 150w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/active-denial-system-500x333.jpg 500w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/active-denial-system-20x13.jpg 20w" sizes="(max-width: 633px) 100vw, 633px" title="20 Anti-Piracy Weapons Deployed In Ships To Fight Pirates 25"></noscript><p id="caption-attachment-8308" class="wp-caption-text">Active Denial System</p></div>
<p>An <strong>Active Denial System</strong> i.e. an ADS or a pain ray is a weapon used against piracy. It sends a small narrow beam of electromagnetic energy to heat the skin. It is non-lethal and does not cause any permanent damage. The electromagnetic wave can penetrate beneath the skin and cause an unbearable burning sensation making the trespassers or pirates jump overboard. It was developed by the US military and is also known as the heat ray. The working of this device is quite similar to that of a microwave oven. It has a system consisting of a gyrotron that emits the waves at a certain frequency with the help of a reflector.</p><div class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px 0; clear: both;'>
<script type="rocketlazyloadscript" async src="https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script>
<!-- maritime body display ads -->
<ins class="adsbygoogle"
     style="display:block"
     data-ad-client="ca-pub-8158074151468920"
     data-ad-slot="7233289586"
     data-ad-format="auto"
     data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins>
<script type="rocketlazyloadscript">
     (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});
</script></div>

<h3><span id="16_Molotov_Cocktail">16) Molotov Cocktail</span></h3>
<p>A Molotov cocktail is a general term used to refer to any bottle-based improvised incendiary weapon. They are also called <strong>gas bombs, bottle bombs, or firebombs</strong>. Many a time, they are used by the crew of the merchant vessels which are not provided with anti-piracy weapons or security guards. A Molotov cocktail is simply thrown into an approaching pirate boat to disturb their maneuverability by setting it ablaze.</p>
<h3><span id="17_Taser_-_Electric_Shock">17) Taser – Electric Shock</span></h3>
<div id="attachment_8309" style="width: 790px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-8309" class="size-full wp-image-8309" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20780%20519'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Taser" width="780" height="519" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/taser.jpg 780w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/taser-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/taser-768x511.jpg 768w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/taser-150x100.jpg 150w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/taser-500x333.jpg 500w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/taser-20x13.jpg 20w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 780px) 100vw, 780px" title="20 Anti-Piracy Weapons Deployed In Ships To Fight Pirates 26" data-lazy-src="https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/taser.jpg"><noscript><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-8309" class="size-full wp-image-8309" src="https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/taser.jpg" alt="Taser" width="780" height="519" srcset="https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/taser.jpg 780w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/taser-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/taser-768x511.jpg 768w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/taser-150x100.jpg 150w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/taser-500x333.jpg 500w, https://www.maritimemanual.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/taser-20x13.jpg 20w" sizes="(max-width: 780px) 100vw, 780px" title="20 Anti-Piracy Weapons Deployed In Ships To Fight Pirates 26"></noscript><p id="caption-attachment-8309" class="wp-caption-text">Taser. Photo: https://www.whiteman.af.mil/News/Features/Display/Article/326069/security-forces-taser-trained-ready-to-operate/</p><div class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px 0; clear: both;'>
<script type="rocketlazyloadscript" async src="https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script>
<!-- maritime body display ads -->
<ins class="adsbygoogle"
     style="display:block"
     data-ad-client="ca-pub-8158074151468920"
     data-ad-slot="7233289586"
     data-ad-format="auto"
     data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins>
<script type="rocketlazyloadscript">
     (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});
</script></div>
</div>
<p>A taser is a non-lethal weapon that can be used by the crew of a ship in case any pirates manage to get on board. Taser stands for Thomas A. Swift’s Electric Rifle. It is a kind of gun that can be used to give an electric shock to the victim and temporarily cause him or her to lose neuromuscular control.</p>
<h3><span id="18_Anti-Piracy_Fire_Hoses">18) A<strong>nti-Piracy Fire Hoses</strong></span></h3>
<p>Anti-piracy fire hoses are extremely powerful hoses that are effective in fighting against pirates. They shoot out streams of water with high pressures. Some anti-piracy fire hoses may also come with remote control systems. They are non-lethal and do not cause serious injuries. These fire hoses are capable of driving away from the pirates by getting in their eyes and at the same time flooding and attacking their boats at a good rate.</p><div class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px 0; clear: both;'>
<script type="rocketlazyloadscript" async src="https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script>
<!-- maritime body display ads -->
<ins class="adsbygoogle"
     style="display:block"
     data-ad-client="ca-pub-8158074151468920"
     data-ad-slot="7233289586"
     data-ad-format="auto"
     data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins>
<script type="rocketlazyloadscript">
     (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});
</script></div>

<h3><span id="19_Stun_Grenade">19) Stun Grenade</span></h3>
<p>A stun grenade is an anti-piracy device that can produce a loud noise and a blinding flash of light. The flash of light has a magnitude of around 7 million candela and the sound is louder than 170 decibels. It is also known as a flash grenade. It is a non-lethal weapon.</p>
<p>They do not cause any major injuries and merely aim at disorienting the senses of the trespassers temporarily. The flash of light is as mentioned before capable of blinding the victim for a few seconds and also temporarily deafens him or her causing a loss of balance.</p><div class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px 0; clear: both;'>
<script type="rocketlazyloadscript" async src="https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script>
<!-- maritime body display ads -->
<ins class="adsbygoogle"
     style="display:block"
     data-ad-client="ca-pub-8158074151468920"
     data-ad-slot="7233289586"
     data-ad-format="auto"
     data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins>
<script type="rocketlazyloadscript">
     (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});
</script></div>

<h3><span id="20_Dazzle_Gun">20) Dazzle Gun</span></h3>
<p>Dazzle gun is another non-lethal weapon similar to a stun grenade. It uses intense directed radiation to disable its target temporarily with flash blindness. These targets can be humans as well as sensors. It emits infrared lights and does not cause any long-term damage to the eye. It has found good use in the marine world, as an anti-piracy measure. Here, these guns are used to dazzle the pirates.</p>
